<ThingDef ParentName="ResourceBase">
  <defName>Aluminium</defName>
  <label>Bauxite Ore</label>
  <description>Bauxite is the ore form of Aluminium. Aluminum is a silvery white, soft, nonmagnetic, ductile metal that is remarkable for the metal's low density and for its ability to resist corrosion due to the phenomenon of passivation. Unlike other raw ores, the smelting of Aluminum cannot be done by hand as the process requires electricity to work. Aluminum is paramagnetic (it becomes attracted to magnetic metals to strengthen the magnetic bond).</description>
